        <abstract>
            <p>Gratified by JDD’s opinion of his work.</p>
            <p>Discusses problem of homologies of cirripede larva in first stage and reasons for his view.</p>
            <p>JDD’s information on corals was just what CD needed.</p> 
<p>Would like specimen of blind cave rat described by B. Silliman [Jr] ["On the Mammoth Cave of Kentucky", <hi rend="italic">Am. J. Sci.</hi> 2d ser. 11 (1851): 336] for Waterhouse to examine.</p> 
            <p>Discusses origin of Australian valleys; he disagrees with JDD’s river-erosion hypothesis.</p>
        </abstract>
